4.454+01:00\">3.42pm <span class=\"timezone\">AEST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/mythor/statuses/390696995414749185\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Bravely ventured outside for another photo. Yes, that’s the sun again! <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23nofilter&amp;src=hash\">#nofilter</a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23bushfire&amp;src=hash\">#bushfire</a> <a href=\"http://t.co/gLJradOIea\">pic.twitter.com/gLJradOIea</a></p>— Matthew Sharpe (@mythor) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/mythor/statuses/390696995414749185\">October 17, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f69cae4b0ebb74892f379\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T05:38:48.399+01:00\">3.38pm <span class=\"timezone\">AEST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/robrfs/statuses/390697385166245888\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Reports of homes being lost across several fire grounds. Still have several hours of unpredictable fire activity. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23nswfires&amp;src=hash\">#nswfires</a></p>— Rob Rogers (@robrfs) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/robrfs/statuses/390697385166245888\">October 17, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f684fe4b0010b6627a8fd\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T05:37:05.340+01:00\">3.37pm <span class=\"timezone\">AEST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p><a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/world/australia\">Australia</a>'s early&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/world/bushfires\">bushfires</a>&nbsp;this year may be part of an ongoing trend towards an increase in both the overall fire danger and the length of the bushfire season, writes Guardian Australia's data journalist Nick Evershed.</p> <p>You can read <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/news/datablog/2013/sep/27/australia-bushfire-weather-increase\">his analysis of a report by the bushfire co-operative research centre here</a>. It comes down to high rain levels followed by high temperatures, both of which Australia has seen lately.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f66b5e4b0760efba2aec7\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T05:31:41.901+01:00\">3.31pm <span class=\"timezone\">AEST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The smoke from the bushfires is playing havoc (again) with the bureau of meteorology radar. Thick plumes are showing up as rain.</p> <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"gu-fc-20d6f5ac-5cb3-4eba-8016-88c4f58bb1f2\"> <img src=\"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/10/17/1381984207893/77527389-cd0f-4e94-983c-766a88353fed-382x420.png\" alt=\"bom radar\" width=\"382\" height=\"420\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption>Thick smoke plumes from the Blue Mountains and Shoalhaven fires show up as rain on the bureau of meteorology radar. Photograph: /Bureau of Meteorology</figcaption> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f65d0e4b0010b6627a8fc\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T05:23:38.136+01:00\">3.23pm <span class=\"timezone\">AEST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The Springwood fire has or will shortly hit the town of Yellow Rock. Residents have been advised to take shelter.</p> <p>That fire is currently being fought by&nbsp;50 firefighters on scene supported by four aircraft and 11 fire trucks.</p> <p>Further north, students in Williamtown and Cabbage Tree have been evacuated as areas as the Heatherbrae fire continues to burn.</p> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T05:24:09.734+01:00\">at 3.24pm AEST</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-525f6579e4b0bbc67cfff3cf\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T05:20:52.761+01:00\">3.20pm <span class=\"timezone\">AEST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Newcastle airport is closed until further notice, a statement on their website reads.</p> <p>Earlier today they advised passengers &quot;to not come to the airport and to contact their airline for flight details.&quot;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f6492e4b0010b6627a8fb\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T05:18:13.174+01:00\">3.18pm <span class=\"timezone\">AEST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Nowra resident Brad Gully has described the situation as seeming &quot;like January all over again.&quot;</p> <p>He hasn't received any advice to evacuate, but told me that he has &quot;always had a plan in place.&quot;</p> <p>&quot;Including safe house for my 6 rescued doggies. Coming from a city (Adelaide) no experience with fires so [it's] all new to me. At the end of day my theory is simple - take your documents and valuables. Save lives. Everything else can be replaced.&quot;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f6433e4b0bbc67cfff3ce\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T05:15:19.228+01:00\">3.15pm <span class=\"timezone\">AEST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>NSW Police have called on people to delay travel in affected areas &quot;unless crucial&quot;.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f6305e4b0010b6627a8fa\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T05:09:43.776+01:00\">3.09pm <span class=\"timezone\">AEST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/GiacomoArnott/statuses/390686123242307585\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Photo posted by a friend on Facebook from inside the RAAF base <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Heatherbrae&amp;src=hash\">#Heatherbrae</a> <a href=\"https://twitter.com/1233newcastle\">@1233newcastle</a> <a href=\"http://t.co/gAQPjNWmaw\">pic.twitter.com/gAQPjNWmaw</a></p>— Giacomo Arnott (@GiacomoArnott) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/GiacomoArnott/statuses/390686123242307585\">October 17, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f6289e4b0bbc67cfff3cd\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T05:08:47.719+01:00\">3.08pm <span class=\"timezone\">AEST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Several roads have been closed around these bushfires, including both&nbsp;directions of the Hume Highway between Mittagong and Bargo in the Southern Highlands.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f612ee4b0ebb74892f373\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T05:06:11.064+01:00\">3.06pm <span class=\"timezone\">AEST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The ABC is reporting that one house has been destroyed in Bargo.</p> <p>Ellison primary school in Springwood has been evacuated.</p> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T05:06:52.575+01:00\">at 3.06pm AEST</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-525f60aae4b0ebb74892f372\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T05:00:30.783+01:00\">3.00pm <span class=\"timezone\">AEST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>A <a href=\"http://www.rfs.nsw.gov.au/dsp_more_info.cfm?CON_ID=21504&amp;CAT_ID=684\">seventh emergency warning</a> has been issued in the Camden area for a grass fire at Varroville.&nbsp;</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f5e2fe4b0bbc67cfff3cb\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T04:49:38.988+01:00\">2.49pm <span class=\"timezone\">AEST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Spokeswoman for the bureau of meteorology, Deryn Griffiths, spoke to Guardian Australia a short time ago about the southerly change making its way towards Sydney and how it will impact on the Hunter region and Blue Mountains, where there are currently serious bushfires.</p> <p>“The main thing of interest is the timing of the change and exactly what way that will come through, which is not always good news for fire agencies,” she said.</p> <p>“The time of that change coming through the main Blue Mountains area is most likely in the next three hours… Through the Hunter it’s going to be more early evening - right through the Hunter region by 10 o’ clock.”</p> <p>Griffiths said the wind will remain a strong southerly on the coast, but may swing more westerly in inland areas. She said fire agencies are aware of the wind change and will be making plans accordingly.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f5bfee4b0760efba2aec5\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T04:43:30.847+01:00\">2.43pm <span class=\"timezone\">AEST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Current warnings are as follows:</p> <p><strong>Emergency warnings:</strong></p> <p><a href=\"http://www.rfs.nsw.gov.au/dsp_more_info.cfm?CON_ID=21488&amp;CAT_ID=684\">Lithgow</a></p> <p><a href=\"http://www.rfs.nsw.gov.au/dsp_more_info.cfm?CON_ID=21503&amp;CAT_ID=684\">Muswellbrook</a></p> <p><a href=\"http://www.rfs.nsw.gov.au/dsp_more_info.cfm?CON_ID=21500&amp;CAT_ID=684\">Springwood&nbsp;</a><a href=\"http://www.rfs.nsw.gov.au/dsp_more_info.cfm?CON_ID=21503&amp;CAT_ID=684\">,&nbsp;</a><a href=\"http://www.rfs.nsw.gov.au/dsp_more_info.cfm?CON_ID=21500&amp;CAT_ID=684\">Blue Mountains</a></p> <p><a href=\"http://www.rfs.nsw.gov.au/dsp_more_info.cfm?CON_ID=21494&amp;CAT_ID=684\">Heatherbrae</a></p> <p><a href=\"http://www.rfs.nsw.gov.au/dsp_more_info.cfm?CON_ID=21499&amp;CAT_ID=684\">South Nowra&nbsp;</a></p> <p><a href=\"http://www.rfs.nsw.gov.au/dsp_more_info.cfm?CON_ID=21495&amp;CAT_ID=684\">Balmoral Village, Southern Highlands</a></p> <p><strong>Watch and act:</strong></p> <p><a href=\"http://www.rfs.nsw.gov.au/dsp_more_info.cfm?CON_ID=21493&amp;CAT_ID=684\">Singleton</a></p> <p><a href=\"http://www.rfs.nsw.gov.au/dsp_more_info.cfm?CON_ID=21501&amp;CAT_ID=684\">Mt Victoria, Blue Mountains</a></p> <p><strong>Advice:</strong></p> <p><a href=\"http://www.rfs.nsw.gov.au/dsp_more_info.cfm?CON_ID=21474&amp;CAT_ID=684\">Webbs Creek, Hawkesbu</a>ry</p> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T04:44:10.304+01:00\">at 2.44pm AEST</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-525f5b77e4b0ebb74892f371\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T04:39:19.596+01:00\">2.39pm <span class=\"timezone\">AEST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Six emergency warnings are now current in NSW, after the NSW RFS issued a warning for a fire&nbsp;burning in Muswellbrook near Blackjack Mountain north west of Newcastle.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f5b0ce4b0ebb74892f370\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T04:35:48.485+01:00\">2.35pm <span class=\"timezone\">AEST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/illawarramerc/statuses/390682238368501760\"> <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>2.30pm BALMORAL UPDATE: The structure that was destroyed by fire may have been a shed. Fire crews cannot get in the area to confirm.</p>— Illawarra Mercury (@illawarramerc) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/illawarramerc/statuses/390682238368501760\">October 17, 2013</a></blockquote> </figure> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f5786e4b0010b6627a8f9\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T04:25:12.049+01:00\">2.25pm <span class=\"timezone\">AEST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>A <strong>fifth emergency warning</strong> has been issued in NSW. There are also two watch and act advisories and one advisory.</p> <p>The fifth warning is a revision of the fire at Yanderra and Balmoral in the Southern Highlands. &quot;There are reports that the fire has or soon will impact Yanderra,&quot; reads the RFS statement.</p> <p>Residents of Yanderra have been told to leave now if they can, otherwise to take shelter.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f55a3e4b0010b6627a8f8\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T04:19:52.254+01:00\">2.19pm <span class=\"timezone\">AEST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>All aircraft that were previously battling the Lithgow fires have been grounded due to dangerous winds, according to the RFS deputy commissioner - director operations, Rob Rogers.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f51ede4b0010b6627a8f6\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T04:07:45.215+01:00\">2.07pm <span class=\"timezone\">AEST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>This is a mirror of the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.rfs.nsw.gov.au/dsp_content.cfm?cat_id=683\">NSW Rural Fire Service</a>&nbsp;Current Fires and Incidents map. It should be at most a few minutes behind.</p> <p><strong>Disclaimer</strong>: This information is extracted from the NSW Rural Fire Service Incident Database. It is not 'real time' information, but is provided as a general indication of current activity.</p> <p>Please listen to your&nbsp;<a href=\"http://abc.net.au/emergency\">ABC Local Radio</a>&nbsp;station if you are in a hazardous situation.</p> <figure class=\"element element-embed\" data-alt=\"NSW Rural Fire Service Current Fires and Incidents map\"> <iframe width=\"460\" height=\"400\" src=\"http://google.org/crisismap/2013-nsw-bushfires?hl=en&amp;llbox=-31.711%2C-34.788%2C154.387%2C149.042&amp;t=ROADMAP&amp;layers=layer0%2C9%2C13%2C5%2C6%2C7%2Clayer1%2C2%2C24&amp;embedded=true\" style=\"border: 1px solid #ccc\"></iframe> </figure> </div> <p class=\"block-time updated-time\">Updated <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T04:08:27.485+01:00\">at 2.08pm AEST</time></p> </div> <div id=\"block-525f5097e4b0760efba2aeb9\" class=\"block\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T03:55:08.300+01:00\">1.55pm <span class=\"timezone\">AEST</span></time> </p> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>The Mount Victoria fire has been revised to a 'watch and act'. An emergency warning has been issued for a grass fire in South Nowra in the Shoalhaven area.</p> </div> </div> <div id=\"block-525f4cb5e4b0bbc67cfff3c1\" class=\"block is-summary\"> <p class=\"block-time published-time\"> <time datetime=\"2013-10-17T03:46:49.476+01:00\">1.46pm <span class=\"timezone\">AEST</span></time> </p> <h2 class=\"block-title\">Summary: four emergency warnings, one 'watch and act' issued in NSW</h2> <div class=\"block-elements\"> <p>Fire services have issued four emergency warnings in New South Wales as serious fires burn in Sydney's Blue Mountains and near Newcastle.</p> <p><strong>A fourth bushfire emergency has been declared in Mount Victoria</strong>, not far from an <a href=\"http://www.rfs.nsw.gov.au/dsp_more_info.cfm?CON_ID=21488&amp;CAT_ID=684\">out of control fire near Lithgow</a> in the Blue Mountains - which has been burning since Wednesday.</p> <p><strong>The Lithgow fire</strong> is threatening homes and residents have been urged to seek shelter as conditions are “deteriorating” according to the rural fire service. Hot and gusty winds are worsening conditions and residents have been warned to take care of flying embers and advised to put out spot fires on their properties.</p> <p>Roads, highways and at least one school have been closed.</p> <p><strong>A <a href=\"http://www.rfs.nsw.gov.au/dsp_more_info.cfm?CON_ID=21494&amp;CAT_ID=684\">fire near Heatherbrae</a></strong> in the Hunter region has breached containment lines, fueled by gusts of up to 7-80kmh. Thick smoke is visible from Newcastle CBD and the city’s airport has been closed.</p> <p>The hot dry and windy weather is expected to continue for another five or six hours at least, rural fire service (RFS) spokesman Joel Kursawe told ABC News.</p> <p>The RFS advises residents near the Heatherbrae fire to evacuate now if they are planning to leave or are not prepared, but only if the way is clear.</p> <p>The same advice has been issued to residents of <strong>Yanderra in the Southern Highlands</strong> where a fire is burning near the village and neighbouring Balmoral. Yanderra residents have been sent an emergency telephone message.</p> <p>A <a href=\"http://www.rfs.nsw.gov.au/dsp_more_info.cfm?CON_ID=21493&amp;CAT_ID=684\">watch and act advisory</a> has also been issued over <strong>a fire east of Singleton</strong>, also in the Hunter region.</p> <p><strong>Near Wiseman’s Ferry in the Hawkesbury region</strong>, more than 30 firefighters and two aircraft are <a href=\"http://www.rfs.nsw.gov.au/dsp_more_info.cfm?CON_ID=21474&amp;CAT_ID=684\">battling a fire</a> which has only been partially contained.</p> <p>The bureau of meteorology (BOM) <a href=\"http://www.bom.gov.au/nsw/warnings/severe.shtml\">earlier issued severe wind and weather warnings</a> for the Hunter, Sydney, Illawarra, Central Tablelands, Southern Tablelands, ACT and Snowy Mountains regions.</p> </div> </div><!-- Guardian Watermark: internal-code/content/420208459|2013-10-17T14:03:15Z|757395910121fe2b5f5e304e9d709a650b4775b6 -->",
